' Blob ID: f797e4cf4db74211a574f3b1a9ad95ed882a128f
' Original Path: /PB-749 - Notifications to encourage a deposit in Goals or Investments/sequences/PB-749 UC4 - Update a Banner on System Management.puml
' Source: World of Code

@startuml
'diagram parameters'
autonumber
'skinparam dpi 300
skinparam LegendBackgroundColor #white

'diagram title'
title PB-749 UC4 - Update a Banner on System Management

'a list of the actors and participants'
actor "System Management" as UI
box "Next Platform"
participant "Core Next" as Next
database "Next Database" as DB
end box
participant "Core Bradesco" as BR

'a brief description of the diagram'
legend top
-- \t**Abstract:**\t --
This use case will be responsible to update an existing banner on Next.
This endpoint is not responsible for deleting a record. To do this, it
must use the use case 5 - Delete a Banner on System Management.
However, in this use case, SM may enable or disable Banner.
end legend

UI->Next: PUT /v1/notification/banner/{bannerID}
activate Next
note right UI
System Management will call this new endpoint
passing all the fields necessary to update an
existing Banner. The fields are:
# BANNER_ID
# BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE_ID
# TEMPLATE_HEADER
# TEMPLATE_BODY
# ENABLE_IND
end note

Next->DB: check if this Banner exists on BANNER table
note right Next
Core Next will check if this Banner exists on BANNER table
end note
activate DB
DB->Next: response
deactivate DB

alt if the Banner exists
  Next->DB: check if exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE received on requisition on BANNER table
  note right Next #orange
  **Note to developers**
  Core Next will check if exists any Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE on BANNER
  table. We can only have one enabled Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE. For this
  rule, we should disregard the records that are with DELETE_FLG enabled and the Card itself.
  end note
  activate DB
  DB->Next: response
  deactivate DB
    alt if exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE
      note right Next
      If exists any Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE passed by App,
      we will throw back an error to App side.
      end note
      Next->UI: error
      note right UI #pink
      **HTTP code:** 422
      end note
    else if don't exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE
      note right Next
      If the defensive checks pass, then we will update the register on BANNER table.
      end note
      Next->DB: update the register on BANNER table
      activate DB
      DB->Next: success
      deactivate DB
      Next->UI: success
      note right UI #lightblue
      **HTTP code:** 200
      end note
    end alt
  else if the Banner don't exists
    Next->UI: error
    note right UI #pink
    If the Banner don't exists on
    BANNER table, then we will
    throw back an error to SM.
    **HTTP code:** 404
    end note
end alt

deactivate Next
@enduml
